  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 3 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 14 high, 2 medium, 23 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR); plus 11 other bases. 2 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, fog / freezing fog and very low visibility  — most notably around London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR). Network hotspots: Tromsø Airport, Langnes (TOS/ENTC), Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Lisbon Humberto Delgado (LIS/LPPT). Primary drivers: thunderstorm / convective risk, snow / blowing snow and mist. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and 9 others.",
